==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Unsting
<hw>Un*sting"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[1st pref.
<ets>un-</ets> + <ets>sting</ets>.]</ety> <def>To disarm of a sting; to
remove the sting of.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧Elegant
dissertations on virtue and vice . . . will not <xex>unsting</xex>
calamity.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>J. M. Mason.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unstitch</ent>⟦br⟧
